---
/*
 * Forces the docs to dark, overriding Starlight's stored-theme / OS-preference
 * logic. reedly.ai is dark-only (src/styles/global.css declares
 * `color-scheme: dark`), so a light docs page would be the only light surface on
 * the domain — and our Starlight palette only defines the navy scale, which in
 * light mode left a navy shell wrapping light code blocks.
 *
 * Paired with the ThemeSelect override, which renders nothing.
 */
---

{/* Inlined rather than bundled — same reason as Starlight's own provider: avoid FOUC. */}
<script is:inline>
  document.documentElement.dataset.theme = 'dark';
  // Starlight's ThemeSelect calls into this global. We render no picker, but keep
  // a no-op so any future Starlight internal that expects it cannot throw.
  window.StarlightThemeProvider = { updatePickers() {} };
</script>
